  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project summary:
The project aims at promoting corporate transparency in the business sector through conducting a Transparency in Corporate Reporting report (TRAC) in Vietnam, based on the methodology developed by Transparency International (TI). This project will use TRAC#s findings and recommendations to advocate companies to gradually apply international anti-corruption measures and to publicly disclose their Country By Country Reporting. Thus, the project will contribute to enhancing the role of business sector in anti-corruption and to improving tax governance in Vietnam.
Project long term goal:
Enhanced public disclosure by large companies in Vietnam of their Country By Country Reporting (CBCR) by following the TRAC report 2018# recommendations.
Main objectives:
# Increase awareness and understanding of companies and other stakeholders (including media, government officials and civil society) of the benefits of greater corporate transparency.
# Improve disclosure practices of largest companies in Vietnam in anti-corruption reporting.
Project Beneficiaries
# Direct beneficiaries: Companies;
# Indirect beneficiaries: government (anti-corruption agencies, law makers), business sector (business regulatory bodies, executive board members, investors, and employees).</narrative>
  </description>
